<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="136">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181639" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole longior Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole longior Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longior">longior</taxonomicName>
, longer, referring to the head shape of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="136">
diagnosis Closest to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33655" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cavifrons Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cavifrons Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavifrons">cavifrons</taxonomicName>
, somewhat less similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33564" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole aberrans Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole aberrans Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">aberrans</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33902" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obnixa Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obnixa Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obnixa">obnixa</taxonomicName>
, distinguished as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="136">
Major: head markedly elongate (Head Length/Head Width 1.47), and bicolored (see under Color below); dorsal posterior half of head profile flat; frontal lobes in full-face view taper anteriorly into blunt acute angles; carinulae originating on frontal lobes reach well past midpoint between eyes and occiput; mesosomal convexity in side view reduced, obliquely angular; propodeal spines denticulate; promesonotum smooth and shiny. Minor: nearly identical to minor of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33655" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cavifrons Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cavifrons Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavifrons">cavifrons</taxonomicName>
(q.v.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="136">Measurements (mm) Lectotype major: HW 0.72, HL 1.06, SL 0.30, EL 0.06, PW 0.50. Paralectotype minor: HW 0.50, HL 0.58, SL 0.36, EL 0.04, PW 0.32.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="136">color Major: strikingly bicolored, with anterior fourth of head dark brown, and rest of body medium yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="136">Minor: concolorous light yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="136">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
